transcription.text:

Speaker 2: Hi, I need to cancel that subscription.

Speaker 1: Sure. Yes, sir, let me pull up your information. Can I get your phone number associated with the prescription?

Speaker 2: Probably 316-204-7000.

Speaker 1: Okay, and the first and last name, please.

Speaker 2: Chris Sheet.

Speaker 1: So, Chris, I don't see you on a recurring currently. You just have your first order right now.

Speaker 2: Right, and I'm just going to go ahead and cancel that.

Speaker 1: Well, I can't cancel it. Is there an issue going on because you haven't received it? Is it the holdup with the doctor?

Speaker 2: No, I just kind of need the money more.

Speaker 1: Okay, so the order that you placed on the 18th, you just want me to go ahead and cancel that?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: So you don't want it at all?

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: Okay. Give me one second. I know there's a holdup with the doctor. I just need to confirm what was going on so they just don't accidentally send it. Bear with me here, okay?

Speaker 2: Yeah, okay. Have you taken it off the card yet?

Speaker 1: So it's been a hold. It's a hold on the charge on the 18th.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: They are, right. Yeah, they are.

Speaker 1: And you just don't want it?

Speaker 2: No, I just kind of need the money right now more than anything.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, I went ahead and canceled that and refunded that. So you'll see that on there, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay. I appreciate it. And I'll call you back when I get the money for it.

Speaker 2: Okay. Not a problem.

Speaker 1: Okay.
